## Introducing Today's Project!

### What is Docker?

Docker is an application that lets me package and build custom images, which  
can then be deployed. It manages images for me as well, and it is useful  
because it helps package the application and dependencies so that the app  
works on all servers correctly. I used Docker in this project to run my custom  
image.

### One thing I didn't expect ...

One thing I didn't expect in this project was seeing how quick it is to deploy an  
application using Elastic Beanstalk.

### This project took me ...

This project took me approximately 2 hours, including demo and troubleshooting  
time. The challenging part was when I was running into errors on Beanstalk  
because of IAM policies. It was most rewarding to see my web app being  
deployed live.

<!-- PageBreak -->

