<!-- PageHeader="nextwork.org" -->

## Understanding Containers and Docker

### Containers

Containers are tools for packaging applications in a way that is easy for  
developers to run. They are useful because it helps developers/engineers to  
share their work more efficiently.

A container image is a built Dockerfile.

### Docker

Docker is a platform for creating and managing containers. Docker Desktop is a  
software for using Docker; it makes working with Docker easy.

The Docker daemon is the engine for Docker that receives commands sent  
through clients (for example, clicks in the docker desktops or text commands  
sent in the terminal), and it creates and manages the containers.

<!-- PageBreak -->

