## Running an Nginx Image

Nginx is a proxy web server that helps with serving web content.

The command I ran to start a new container was `docker run -d -p 80:80 nginx`.  
`-d` means I am running the application in the background, and I am matching the  
host port 80 to the container's port 80, which is why I ran `-p 80:80.`

