### Creating a Custom Image

The Dockerfile contains the instructions that tell Docker how to build my custom  
container image.

My Dockerfile tells Docker three things:  
1. The custom container image uses the latest version of the nginx container image at its base  
2. Then it makes modifications by replacing the default nginx welcome page with my custom `index.html`  
3. It then tells Docker: *The container listens on port 80.*

Port 80 is the default HTTP port for web servers (like Nginx).

The command I used to build a custom image with my Dockerfile was:

```
docker build -t my-web-app .
```

The `.` at the end tells Docker to look at the current working directory for the instructions.  
Docker automatically scans for a file named `Dockerfile` unless I specify `-f`.

