## Running My Custom Image

There was an error when I ran my custom image because I tried to map to the  
container's port 80, but a running container was already using port 80. I resolved  
this by stopping the running container so I could start the new one.

In this example:

- The **container image** is the blueprint that tells Docker the application code,  
  dependencies, and libraries that should go into a container.  
- The **container** is the actual software created from this image, running the  
  web server displaying your `index.html` file.

